Package gameObjects

Class Robot

java.lang.Object
gameObjects.Robot
public class Robot
extends java.lang.Object
This class represents robot on the overall game in this project. The purpose of this class is to represent all information in the robot, so that the robots can gather as much fruits as possible in the fastest and most efficient way.
Author:
Meir Nizri

  • Method Details

    • update

      public void update​(java.lang.String robot_Json)
      Because there are fixed values that do not change in the robot after added to the game, the robot values update is partial.
      Parameters:
      robot_Json - - Json string the game server return with command "getRobots()", containing information about the robot.

    • getDest

      public int getDest()
      Gets the dest node key the robot going to. If equals -1 it means that it has reached its destination and needs to define what the next move will be.
      Returns:
      the dest node key.

    • getLocation

      public Point3D getLocation()

    • getPath

      public java.util.LinkedList<node_data> getPath()
      Gets the path of the robot. This path is LinkedList of nodes where the robot keeps all the nodes it needs to pass through until he reaches next fruit.
      Returns:
      the path of the robot.

      Parameters:
      pathToAdd - - the new path.

    • nextMove

      public int nextMove()
      Calculates the next node the robot goes to. If robot path is not empty then return the first node in path, and delete this node from path. But if the path is empty, then the robot will remain in its current location.
      Returns:
      the key of the next node.

    • getNextMove

      public int getNextMove()
      Calculates the next node the robot goes to. If robot path is not empty then return the first node in path. But if the path is empty, then the robot will remain in its current location.
      Returns:
      the key of the next node.

    • getValue

      public double getValue()
      Returns:
      how much points the robot collected so far.
